               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-252-person2353">
                  JOSEPH 
                  BURKE
               <interp inst="t18290409-252-person2353" type="surname" value="BURKE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-252-person2353" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-252-person2353" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live on the first floor of a house opposite the prosecutor's. About a quarter past three o'clock on the 6th of April, I was looking through my window, and saw the prisoner looking in the prosecutor's window - he went to the door, and unhooked the two pairs of shoes - before I could open the window he was gone; I went down, and saw the prosecutor; we went to Castle-street, and saw the prisoner loitering about, as if he was coming back again; I do not know what became of the shoes; I am sure that he is the lad - he was taken in three or four minutes.</p>
